From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rurix Godot Bridge <rurix@example.invalid>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 22:50:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Add the GRX-010 tonemap recording-smoke and gated real-pass
 opt-in arms with result writeback scaffold

Stacked on 0001..0012. This is the GRX-010 bridge-recording / real-pass
opt-in slice (the GRX-009 0008+0009+0010 layers merged into one patch for
the tonemap pass). It is a bring-up gate, not a default enablement, and it
does not change the shipping fallback semantics.

- modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp: adds three per-pass opt-in
  settings that all default to false and are separate from
  rendering/rurix_accel/passes/tonemap/enabled:
  .../tonemap/dispatch_recording_smoke (harness-only recording-smoke marker
  arm), .../tonemap/dispatch_real_pass (the gated REAL tonemap pass arm),
  and .../tonemap/real_pass_force_capability_downgrade (a harness-only
  forced-failure knob for the fallback red/green leg).
- modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.h: declares the reserved tonemap
  real-pass arm flag RXGD_CAP_TONEMAP_REAL_PASS (bridge value 1 << 4)
  carried in RxGdCaps.flags. This reuses the existing flags field: the C
  ABI struct layout and RXGD_ABI_VERSION are unchanged.
- modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp: try_create_session() sets
  RXGD_CAP_TONEMAP_REAL_PASS ONLY when the tonemap dispatch_real_pass
  opt-in is enabled, and clears RXGD_CAP_SHADER_INT64 ONLY when the
  harness-only tonemap real_pass_force_capability_downgrade knob is enabled
  (making the bridge tonemap preflight fail closed with
  unsupported_device for the forced-failure leg). try_record_tonemap()
  emits a distinctive RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_TONEMAP_REAL_PASS marker only when
  rxgd_record_pass actually returned RXGD_STATUS_OK on the real-pass arm,
  and the RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_TONEMAP_RECORD marker only under the
  harness-only dispatch_recording_smoke opt-in, so a real-pass success is
  never misreported as a recording-smoke run and vice versa.
- renderer_scene_render_rd.cpp Tonemap call site: when try_record_tonemap()
  returned true on the real-pass arm, the Rurix bridge has already
  dispatched the tonemap kernel INTO the real LDR destination
  ID3D12Resource* resolved in patch 0012, so the LINEAR + linear_to_srgb
  subset result is physically written into the destination texture. The
  result writeback SCAFFOLD prints a machine-readable
  RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_TONEMAP_REAL_PASS_WRITEBACK marker recording that
  writeback, then deliberately clears rurix_recorded_tonemap so the FULL
  native Godot tonemapper still runs as the continuation/backstop: the
  kernel covers only the LINEAR tonemapper with the SDR convert_to_srgb leg
  (no auto exposure, glow, FXAA, BCS, color correction, debanding, or other
  tonemap modes; GPU math parity is still pending measurement), so the
  native raster pass re-renders the frame and the rendered image can never
  change while the scaffold is in place.

The bridge fails closed on the real-pass arm: it runs the runtime binding
preflight, the dispatch eligibility gate, the per-slot kernel-binding-kind
conformance check, and the math-parity gate, and returns
RXGD_STATUS_FALLBACK with a machine-readable RXGD_TONEMAP_REAL_PASS_BLOCKED
diagnostic naming the FIRST missing prerequisite; the real dispatch is only
linked under the test-only d3d12-recording-shim bridge feature, so the
shipping feature-off bridge fails closed with real_dispatch_path_not_linked
even when every software gate passes. This does not change
RXGD_ABI_VERSION, does not enable the pass by default (all four tonemap
per-pass settings still default to false), does not flip real_gpu_pass to
true by itself, and makes no visual, measured-telemetry, GPU-timestamp, or
performance claim by itself.
---
diff --git a/modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp b/modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp
index 27aa305..bc394ba 100644
--- a/modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp
+++ b/modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp
@@ -56,6 +56,39 @@ void initialize_rurix_accel_module(ModuleInitializationLevel p_level) {
 	// RXGD_PASS_TONEMAP, so the native tonemap path keeps rendering in
 	// practice and no acceleration is claimed.
 	GLOBAL_DEF_BASIC("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/tonemap/enabled", false);
+	// GRX-010: harness-only Godot-runtime tonemap bridge dispatch recording
+	// smoke opt-in (0008-level, template copy of the luminance
+	// dispatch_recording_smoke). Defaults to false so the shipping build
+	// never arms the recording-smoke marker path. It only gates the
+	// module-side RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_TONEMAP_RECORD marker; the bridge
+	// record path itself is only linked when the loaded rurix_godot.dll is
+	// built with the test-only d3d12-recording-shim feature AND the
+	// dispatch_real_pass opt-in below armed the fail-closed real-pass gate.
+	// The default build/config never enables it and the shipping
+	// (feature-off) bridge still returns RXGD_STATUS_FALLBACK for
+	// RXGD_PASS_TONEMAP.
+	GLOBAL_DEF_BASIC("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/tonemap/dispatch_recording_smoke", false);
+	// GRX-010: opt-in gated REAL tonemap pass bring-up arm (0009-level).
+	// Defaults to false so the shipping build never arms the real-pass
+	// attempt. Even when enabled the bridge runs its runtime binding
+	// preflight, dispatch eligibility, per-slot kernel-binding-kind
+	// conformance, and math-parity checks and keeps returning
+	// RXGD_STATUS_FALLBACK (with a machine-readable
+	// RXGD_TONEMAP_REAL_PASS_BLOCKED diagnostic naming the first missing
+	// prerequisite) unless every check passes AND a runtime-mappable real
+	// dispatch path is linked (d3d12-recording-shim builds only); the
+	// shipping feature-off bridge fails closed with
+	// real_dispatch_path_not_linked, so the native Godot tonemap path keeps
+	// rendering.
+	GLOBAL_DEF_BASIC("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/tonemap/dispatch_real_pass", false);
+	// GRX-010: harness-only forced-failure knob for the tonemap fallback
+	// red/green leg (0009-level template of the luminance
+	// real_pass_force_capability_downgrade). When enabled the module clears
+	// the shader-int64 capability it advertises to the bridge, so the
+	// bridge tonemap preflight fails closed with unsupported_device while
+	// the native Godot tonemap path keeps rendering. Defaults to false;
+	// never enabled by the shipping build/config.
+	GLOBAL_DEF_BASIC("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/tonemap/real_pass_force_capability_downgrade", false);
 
 #if defined(D3D12_ENABLED)
 	if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/enabled")) {
diff --git a/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp b/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp
index dcbc15a..897a2e5 100644
--- a/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp
+++ b/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp
@@ -217,6 +217,23 @@ void RurixAccelD3D12Hooks::try_create_session() {
 	if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/luminance_reduction/real_pass_force_capability_downgrade")) {
 		caps.flags &= ~RXGD_CAP_SHADER_INT64;
 	}
+	// GRX-010: arm the opt-in gated REAL tonemap pass attempt ONLY when the
+	// default-false tonemap dispatch_real_pass opt-in is enabled. The bridge
+	// still fails closed (fallback + RXGD_TONEMAP_REAL_PASS_BLOCKED first
+	// missing prerequisite) unless every gate passes AND the
+	// d3d12-recording-shim real dispatch path is linked and completes; this
+	// is a bring-up gate, not a default runtime pass.
+	if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/tonemap/dispatch_real_pass")) {
+		caps.flags |= RXGD_CAP_TONEMAP_REAL_PASS;
+	}
+	// GRX-010: harness-only tonemap forced-failure knob. Clearing the
+	// shader-int64 capability makes the bridge tonemap preflight fail
+	// closed with unsupported_device while the native Godot tonemap path
+	// keeps rendering; the fallback red/green leg of the GRX-010 real-pass
+	// enablement smoke verifies exactly this.
+	if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/tonemap/real_pass_force_capability_downgrade")) {
+		caps.flags &= ~RXGD_CAP_SHADER_INT64;
+	}
 	if (adapter_luid_valid) {
 		memcpy(caps.adapter_luid, &adapter_luid, sizeof(adapter_luid));
 	}
@@ -382,6 +399,19 @@ bool RurixAccelD3D12Hooks::try_record_tonemap(uint64_t p_source_native_handle, u
 		}
 		return false;
 	}
+	// GRX-010: only reachable when the bridge's opt-in real-pass arm
+	// actually returned RXGD_STATUS_OK after a real recorded dispatch
+	// (d3d12-recording-shim builds only; the shipping feature-off bridge
+	// always falls back with real_dispatch_path_not_linked first). The
+	// REAL_PASS marker reports the real-pass arm; the RECORD marker belongs
+	// to the harness-only recording smoke opt-in so a real-pass success is
+	// never misreported as a recording-smoke run and vice versa.
+	if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/tonemap/dispatch_real_pass")) {
+		print_line("RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_TONEMAP_REAL_PASS: pass=RXGD_PASS_TONEMAP dispatched=1");
+	}
+	if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/tonemap/dispatch_recording_smoke")) {
+		print_line("RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_TONEMAP_RECORD: pass=RXGD_PASS_TONEMAP recorded=1");
+	}
 	return true;
 }
 
diff --git a/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.h b/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.h
index 39e76fc..98efe05 100644
--- a/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.h
+++ b/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.h
@@ -33,6 +33,16 @@
 // recorded fallback reason and an RXGD_REAL_PASS_BLOCKED diagnostic until
 // a runtime-mappable real dispatch path exists.
 #define RXGD_CAP_LUMINANCE_REAL_PASS 8u
+// GRX-010 opt-in tonemap real-pass arm carried in RxGdCaps.flags (ABI v1,
+// no struct layout change; bridge value 1 << 4). Set only when the
+// default-false rendering/rurix_accel/passes/tonemap/dispatch_real_pass
+// opt-in is enabled. Setting it never on its own makes the bridge return
+// RXGD_STATUS_OK: the fail-closed TonemapGate runs preflight ->
+// eligibility -> binding-kind -> math-parity -> linked-dispatch checks and
+// returns RXGD_STATUS_FALLBACK with an RXGD_TONEMAP_REAL_PASS_BLOCKED
+// diagnostic unless every check passes AND the d3d12-recording-shim real
+// dispatch path is linked and completes.
+#define RXGD_CAP_TONEMAP_REAL_PASS 16u
 
 typedef struct RxGdCaps {
 	uint32_t abi_version;
diff --git a/servers/rendering/renderer_rd/renderer_scene_render_rd.cpp b/servers/rendering/renderer_rd/renderer_scene_render_rd.cpp
index e98b098..247b1af 100644
--- a/servers/rendering/renderer_rd/renderer_scene_render_rd.cpp
+++ b/servers/rendering/renderer_rd/renderer_scene_render_rd.cpp
@@ -890,6 +890,24 @@ void RendererSceneRenderRD::_render_buffers_post_process_and_tonemap(const Rende
 				if (rurix_source_native_handle != 0 && rurix_dest_native_handle != 0) {
 					rurix_recorded_tonemap = D3D12Hooks::get_singleton()->try_record_tonemap(rurix_source_native_handle, (uint32_t)MAX(color_size.x, 0), (uint32_t)MAX(color_size.y, 0), rurix_dest_native_handle, (uint32_t)MAX(tonemap.dest_texture_size.x, 0), (uint32_t)MAX(tonemap.dest_texture_size.y, 0), tonemap.exposure, tonemap.white, tonemap.luminance_multiplier);
 				}
+				if (rurix_recorded_tonemap) {
+					// GRX-010 result writeback SCAFFOLD (0010-level). The
+					// Rurix bridge dispatched the tonemap kernel directly
+					// into the real LDR destination ID3D12Resource*, so the
+					// LINEAR + linear_to_srgb subset result is physically
+					// written into the destination texture. Record that
+					// writeback with a machine-readable marker, then keep the
+					// FULL native Godot tonemapper as the
+					// continuation/backstop: the kernel covers only the
+					// LINEAR tonemapper with the SDR convert_to_srgb leg (no
+					// auto exposure, glow, FXAA, BCS, color correction,
+					// debanding, or other tonemap modes; GPU math parity is
+					// still pending measurement), so the native raster pass
+					// re-renders the frame and the image can never change
+					// while this scaffold is in place.
+					print_line("RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_TONEMAP_REAL_PASS_WRITEBACK: dst=tonemap_destination native_continuation=active scaffold=1");
+					rurix_recorded_tonemap = false;
+				}
 			}
 #endif
 			if (!rurix_recorded_tonemap) {
-- 
2.50.0
